<h2 class="wp-block-heading list-start">Anatomy Of The Shoulder</h2>



<p>The <a href="https://jsesinternational.org/article/S2666-6383(24)00043-4/fulltext" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">shoulder muscle</a> is made up of three parts, or heads. Each of these heads has a unique point of origin and insertion. This gives each head its own function and range of motion. As a result, you need to do specific exercises to target each muscle head.&nbsp;</p>



<p>The three heads of the shoulder muscles are the:</p>



<ul>
<li>Anterior (front) head.</li>



<li>Medial (side) head.</li>



<li>Posterior (rear) head.</li>
</ul>


